## THE OFFICIOUS FLIES.

A <span class="small">FEW</span> dozen flies once attacked a cart-horse
who was feeding quietly in a thicket, and lamented that they were not
more numerous, that they might make him lie down. Presently his skin
began to itch, when he lay down, rolled first on once side and then on
the other, and crushed them all.

